title: PIGEON travels through London on the Northern Line
text: comments Commuters were left stunned after a brave pigeon made its way onto the London Underground and travelled throughout the capital - getting a free lunch in the process. The small animal managed to make its way on the Northern Line as the Tube travelled from Bank to Moorgate. A baffled woman was eating as she stood inside the carriage and was shocked when the bird flew up onto her bag. She was tucking into what looked like a piece of chocolate and offered it to the pigeon - who enjoyed a couple of nibbles. The brave pigeon jumped up on to the woman's bag (left) and was quickly offered some food (right) Stunned passengers reacted in shock as they could only stare in amazement after the bird began eating on the tube. At the end of the clip, the woman could be seen getting off the tube with the pigeon still on her arm. RELATED ARTICLES
